resources.string:
If you have the USA or Canadian version of the YP-G70 then this should be on, otherwise it should be off.

XAA and XAC are USA and Canadian with capacitive home button. All other codes are INT with the physical home button.

 You will have problems with you buttons if this is not set correctly.

Reboot required after switching.
Allows you to double tap on the screen to wake up the device. Note: does not work in deep sleep unless a wakelock is used.
Allows you to swipe the screen, left to right, to wake up the device. Note: does not work in deep sleep unless a wakelock is used.
When you receive a notification and the screen is off the back-light on your capacitive buttons will illuminate. The button back-light will return to normal behavior after you wake the device.
Causes the button-backlights to blink when BLN is enabled.
Uses dnsmasq to force the use of Google\'s DNS servers instead of whatever is assigned by DHCP. Only known to work with Wifi.\n\nNOTE: Disable this if this device is used as a tethering "server"!
If the status bar clock get stuck enable this. WARNING: Do not depend on this to fix the alarm clock. NOTE: Experimental for now.

The In-Call Audio Service runs in the background and when you are on a call. It resets the volume to workaround the low-in-call volume problem. It also detects if you switch to speaker phone and resets the volume for that stream as well.
The BT Tether workaround detects when your connected to a Tethering "server" and runs dhcp on the bt-pan interface and also runs dnsmasq for you automatically; effectively fixing bluetooth tethering.

This option forces the use of the Google software decoder for H.264 video. This fixes issues in the latest release of the official Youtube app. However the switch is system wide and the Google software decoder does not work well when watching HD video such as video captured from the camera app.\n\nBasically: Enable to fix Youtube. Disable for HD video.

I am not sure what benefits this has but this allows you to disable the secondary cpu. It is possible that this may save battery life. Note: I have noticed that disabling it sometimes causes the min and max scaling frequency to both be set at 1000 mhz???(Experimental)
Low Memory Killer - Not Killable Processes: allows you to set a white list of processes in the LMK. LMK will not kill these processes when more memory is needed unless it is absolutely neccessary.
Auto logcat enables automatic dumping of the log to a file in the root of the sdcard. Does not clean up after itself. Should probably keep this off unless I ask you to turn it on.
Auto kmsg enables automatic dumping of the kernel log to a file in the root of the sdcard. Does not clean up after itself. Should probably keep this off unless I ask you to turn it on.
Auto ril log enables automatic dumping of the Radio log to a file in the root of the sdcard. Does not clean up after itself. Should probably keep this off unless I ask you to turn it on.
